text:
*DL/CV Engineer, 48-72k Euro annual [+1-3%], remote*

*The company is on a mission to create virtual training tools for racket sports that help players and coaches realize their full potential*
*<http://clutchapp.io|clutchapp.io>*

Experience with video action recognition / temporal action localization / event detection is required

Responsibilities

We are developing algorithms in the domains of semantic segmentation, object
detection and spatiotemporal action localization. You will work closely with our CTO
on developing our back end AI system. We are a small team with a big vision - it is
important that you take ownership over the product and that you are a team player
that shares the mission with us.

Requirements

 - You have 3+ years industry experience applying ML/DL/CV to tackle
real-world problems;
 - You have experience working with action recognition, temporal localization
and object tracking;
 - You are skilled in explaining and presenting analyses and concepts to both a
technical and a non-technical audience;
 - You have experience working with technologies like PyTorch, Tensorflow,
Docker, SQL and OpenCV;
 - You have excellent experience in Python and strong experience in software
development, writing great code and implementing patterns where they apply;
 - You take ownership and responsibility of the parts of the project you
implement and lead;
 - You are able to work autonomously with little supervision;
 - You’re positive and driven, and a fast learner;
 - You are able to lead a small team of highly skilled engineers.

Is a plus

 - Publications in academic journals;
 - Experience contributing to open-source projects;
 - Experience with the AWS suite;
 - Having a passion for racket sports

apply here <@U833M29T7> or <mailto:p@occurai.com|p@occurai.com> or tg: ufi00

